data.title: I panicked like I have never panicked before

images.description:
So I'm a general contractor who mostly remodels bathrooms, but this was a first. Yesterday, on the final day of a bathroom remodel, I decided to be the first person to use the new toilet (the clients were at work).  

As usual, I did my business while lurking on Imgur, and I flushed the toilet a few times over the course of my poop. When I was finished, I looked over towards the tub and saw brown water with little lettuce-looking chunks coming out of the bathtub drain and filling the damn thing up. I panicked, and the first thing I could think to do was to flush the toilet again (maybe there was a tp clog that I could dislodge). But now the toilet appeared to be clogged, and it started filling to the brim with brown water. Fuck.

I ran around the client's house looking for a plunger, but to no avail. I came back into the bathroom to see AN ACTUAL PIECE OF SHIT FLOATING AROUND IN THE SHOWER. Fuck Fuck Fuck. I remembered that that the waste lines were accessible in the garage and I sprinted downstairs, and that's when I saw it: there was still a rubber plug in the waste line from when the plumbers performed a water leakage test. Still panicking, I ripped the plug out of the waste clean-out and listened in relief as my poop gurgled down the 4 inch pipe. 

Then the fucking pipe "BURPED"  and spit some of the heinous liquid onto my pants. But I wasn't even that mad because I knew that the bathroom wasn't full of my shit anymore. I spent the next hour cleaning the place up, went home, and was too embarrassed to tell anyone. So I'm telling you.

images.description:
I'm from Croatia, in the picture here is a water tower that was bombed in our war for independence in the 90s. That broken tower is one of the images of our war, a symbol of resistance and cruelty.

I've been following the news with Ukraine, and hearing the things Putin says, the narrative that's being pushed there, it's all too familiar. I'm not even going to go into details, it's just early similar.

Something that saddens me is when I go to our public forums, the same people that claim to have fought in our war are right now cheering for Putin. For days now, I've read those people claim Ukraine is not actually a country, or that Crimea belongs with Russia and this and that, and making fun of anyone trying to criticize Putin.

I was young back then, but I remember the sound of sirens, I remember going to bunkers under buildings, picking ups bits of shrapnel in the kitchen, missing out on school because it wasn't safe. I'm lucky it didn't last long. I'm sad it's happening again in Ukraine, I'm sad so many people have already decided that they don't care, I'm even more sad so many have decided to cheer on Putin and will grab on any straw just to derail the topic.

Stay strong Ukraine!

data.title: Not all women need a glass slipper to make dreams true

images.description:
It took a marathon of Mike Rowe's "Dirty Jobs," me hating my career, and the news coverage of Hurricane Maria wiping Puerto Rico out to have me change careers in my 30s.  

I researched electrical tradework, and read that only 2% of electrical workers in the U.S. are women, so much to my mother's chagrin, I stopped doing what I was doing and went back to school.  

Today, I got my card. And the statistic moved upwards internationally, probably by a small margin of such a wee percent.  Took 4.5 years to get here.

Tell the good smart women in your life to do whatever it takes to move a statistic!

Goal set: 2017
Goal achieved: 2022

data.title: The Ukraine Ambassadors chilling mic drop. Seriously wait til the end.
Corporate America Sucks. So I took it for a ride...

images.description:
TL;DR  Job refused to consider cost of living adjustments, completely quit efforts to work and it took them almost 11 months to fire me.

Story Time: I worked for one of the biggest telecom companies in the US. Started in the office, transitioned to Work From Home due to Covid. After half a decade and then some of asking for fair cost of living adjustments I was told no every single time. Was told we were already competitive so nope, not gonna happen. The job I had previously had done a COLA for its employees so I knew their refusal to consider it was bullshit. If they don't value me the right way, I shouldn't be here. So after several years of that, I resolved to quit. But I was going to make them do it.

In early 2021, I killed the motor. I stopped trying and watched my once pristine metrics slowly tank. I sat through coaching after coaching with my sup, him trying methods to make me work harder, me smiling inside knowing that we are wasting our time because my time immersed in this culture has stolen my motivation. And I made it known, too. We had a regular eNPS survey that they say is anonymous, but it isn't. I let them have it in the past year on every single one. Our big manager had the gall to address my comments about COLA's and told us to stop asking. This is when I elevated my efforts. Since our pay was not effected by the quality of our work, just our hours, my path was clear; Escalate until it blows up! >:-D

I invented system problems. Since I had different internet than work provided, I knew they had no in-house way to check whether I was actually in an outage so my home internet developed many frustrating problems during business hours (Which was little more than an unplugged modem cable). I waited days for techs that were never scheduled. I said my headset would not work when it was working fine. I kept feeling like someone with half a brain would see it and figure out what I was doing, but I was 7 months into not trying and still being paid in full for it. I wondered how far I could push it.

I kept expecting a Performance Improvement Plan (PIP) to be issued but eventually, my boss just decided that my magic was gone and he left me alone to put up mediocre numbers, while playing on my gaming PC for the entire shift, not caring about the work at all.

Finally after about 8 months, they started to ask about the headset and it not working. They had finally noticed that I didn't care anymore, so surely my termination was imminent. Internet issues only cropped up when we were exceptionally busy. The holidays were approaching and my boss told me to order a new headset. Support tickets were opened to troubleshoot, but it was a weird gremlin that no one could pin down. Imagine that...  It's not like there were pay raises and more opportunity available for hard work, so why try?

Finally my boss questioned my metrics and said there was something going on. Deep Dives by others in the QC Dept finally revealed my actions of not caring. What I expected to get away with for a month or so, went on for nearly a year. It was 10.5 months after I killed my efforts before they terminated me. It seems A.I. systems that grade you for metrics aren't smart enough to detect actual thinking. What's funny is that he never said why. It was a very short Zoom call where I was informed of being terminated.

I cashed out my stock portfolio I had been building with the company and am going to take the next year off before getting back into the work force again. Thanks Imgur, for allowing me a place to vent my story. Never working for Corp America again. It's only the CEO and Board's friend, certainly not its employees'. I still can't believe it took them as long as it did to catch it. Cheers, you wonderful bastards.

Disclaimer: I did this knowing I was sinking the ship. Please don't do the same unless you are ready for the job to end, too.

images.description:
A tale of two Darths https://imgur.com/gallery/A7NUnJW
Original Post

I like my family, but I'm not really much of a social person. I do family reunions just so my parent won't get mad because I'm not there, so my birthday celebrations are mostly just me waiting for the socially acceptable time for me to leave, without it being awkward since I'm the one who's birthday is being celebrated.

But this year two out of my three brothers got sick with COVID, so we had to skip the entire thing. I had a wonderful day, lots of cake just for the wife and me, no chores to do (because it was my birthday), so I just stayed home all day playing games and watching movies. Just had to pick up the phone every now and then to thank people wishing me a happy birthday.

Best birthday ever :)

PS: my family is ok, my brothers caught omicron and they were all vaccinated by then, so it wasn't life threatening or anything, just mild symptoms. Oh, and my birthday was a month ago, just didn't get around to posting about it lol
